5:["$","$L10",null,{"children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Article\",\"headline\":\"How to Clean Vinyl Records: The Complete Guide for DJs and Collectors\",\"description\":\"Learn how to clean vinyl records properly — from dry brushing to wet cleaning. Protect your collection, improve sound quality, and extend the life of your stylus.\",\"datePublished\":\"April 3, 2025\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"45 Mix Trackr\",\"url\":\"https://www.45mixtrackr.com\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"45 Mix Trackr\",\"url\":\"https://www.45mixtrackr.com\"},\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://www.45mixtrackr.com/blog/how-to-clean-vinyl-records\"}}"}}],["$","article",null,{"className":"max-w-2xl text-white","children":[["$","$L11",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-[#B3B3B3] hover:text-white text-sm mb-8 transition-colors","children":[["$","svg",null,{"className":"w-4 h-4","fill":"currentColor","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","children":["$","path",null,{"d":"M15.41 16.59L10.83 12l4.58-4.59L14 6l-6 6 6 6z"}]}],"All posts"]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-black leading-tight mb-3","children":"How to Clean Vinyl Records: The Complete Guide for DJs and Collectors"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 text-xs text-[#6B6B6B] mb-10","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":"April 3, 2025"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"7 min read"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h2","0",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Introduction"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"A dirty record doesn't just sound worse — it actively damages your stylus. Dust, grease, and grit in the grooves act like sandpaper against the diamond tip, wearing it down with every play. Regular cleaning is one of the most impactful things you can do for both sound quality and the longevity of your equipment."}}],["$","p","2",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"This guide covers every cleaning method, from a quick daily brush to deep wet cleaning for thrift store finds."}}],["$","hr","3",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}],["$","h2","4",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Why Records Get Dirty"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Vinyl is statically charged, which means it attracts dust like a magnet. Every time you play a record, the stylus pushes debris further into the groove. Add fingerprint oils, smoke residue from old venues, and general environmental grime — and even a \"clean\" looking record can be sonically degraded."}}],["$","p","6",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Signs your record needs cleaning:"}}],["$","ul","7",{"className":"list-disc list-outside ml-5 space-y-1 text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","children":[["$","li","0",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Audible crackling or popping that wasn't there before"}}],["$","li","1",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Dull, muffled high frequencies"}}],["$","li","2",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Visible dust or smudges on the playing surface"}}],["$","li","3",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Static shocks when you pick the record up"}}]]}],["$","hr","8",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}],["$","h2","9",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Method 1: Carbon Fiber Brush (Daily Maintenance)"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"The carbon fiber brush is the most important piece of record care equipment a DJ owns. Used before every play, it removes loose surface dust and discharges static."}}],"$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18","$L19","$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21","$L22","$L23","$L24","$L25","$L26","$L27","$L28","$L29","$L2a","$L2b","$L2c","$L2d","$L2e","$L2f","$L30","$L31","$L32","$L33","$L34","$L35","$L36","$L37","$L38","$L39","$L3a","$L3b","$L3c","$L3d"]}],"$L3e","$L3f"]}]]}]
12:["$","p","11",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">How to use it:</strong>"}}]
13:["$","p","12",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"1. Place the brush across the grooves while the record spins on the platter"}}]
14:["$","p","13",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"2. Hold it lightly — don't press down"}}]
15:["$","p","14",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"3. After a few rotations, lift the brush toward the edge to sweep the dust off"}}]
16:["$","p","15",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"4. Never drag loose dust toward the label"}}]
17:["$","p","16",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"This takes 10 seconds and should be a habit before every single play. It won't remove embedded grime, but it prevents surface dust from being pushed deeper into the groove."}}]
18:["$","hr","17",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}]
19:["$","h2","18",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Method 2: Velvet Record Brush"}]
1a:["$","p","19",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Similar to the carbon fiber brush but uses soft velvet fibers to physically lift dust from grooves. Some DJs prefer velvet for its gentle touch on delicate vintage pressings."}}]
1b:["$","p","20",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Use the same technique as the carbon fiber brush — let the record spin and hold the brush lightly across the surface."}}]
1c:["$","hr","21",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}]
1d:["$","h2","22",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Method 3: Wet Cleaning (Record Cleaning Fluid)"}]
1e:["$","p","23",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"For records with visible smudges, embedded grime, or second-hand finds, wet cleaning is necessary. You'll need:"}}]
1f:["$","ul","24",{"className":"list-disc list-outside ml-5 space-y-1 text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","children":[["$","li","0",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Record cleaning fluid (specifically formulated — never use tap water or household cleaners)"}}],["$","li","1",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"A microfiber or velvet cleaning pad"}}],["$","li","2",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"A drying rack or clean surface"}}]]}]
20:["$","p","25",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Process:</strong>"}}]
21:["$","p","26",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"1. Apply a few drops of cleaning fluid to the pad"}}]
22:["$","p","27",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"2. Place the pad on the spinning record, applying light pressure"}}]
23:["$","p","28",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"3. Move the pad with the grooves (not against them) for 3–4 rotations"}}]
24:["$","p","29",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"4. Wipe the residue with the dry side of the pad"}}]
25:["$","p","30",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"5. Let the record fully air-dry before playing"}}]
26:["$","p","31",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Recommended fluids: Mobile Fidelity Sound Lab record cleaning fluid, Spin-Clean solution, or GrooveWasher G2."}}]
27:["$","hr","32",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}]
28:["$","h2","33",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Method 4: Record Cleaning Machine (Best Results)"}]
29:["$","p","34",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"For serious collectors and DJs with large or valuable collections, a vacuum record cleaning machine is the gold standard. It applies fluid, scrubs the grooves with a brush, then vacuums up the dirty fluid — leaving the record truly clean."}}]
2a:["$","p","35",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Top options:</strong>"}}]
2b:["$","ul","36",{"className":"list-disc list-outside ml-5 space-y-1 text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","children":[["$","li","0",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Okki Nokki</strong> — affordable, manual operation, excellent results"}}],["$","li","1",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Nitty Gritty</strong> — reliable workhorse used in many record stores"}}],["$","li","2",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Audio Desk Systeme</strong> — ultrasonic cleaning, the most thorough available"}}]]}]
2c:["$","p","37",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"A single RCM session can transform a crackly thrift store record into something that sounds nearly new."}}]
2d:["$","hr","38",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}]
2e:["$","h2","39",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Method 5: Spin-Clean Record Washer"}]
2f:["$","p","40",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"A budget alternative to a full RCM. The Spin-Clean is a basin with two brushes that clean both sides of the record simultaneously as you rotate it by hand. At around $80, it's the best value wet-cleaning solution available."}}]
30:["$","p","41",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Great for cleaning batches of second-hand records before they go into your collection."}}]
31:["$","hr","42",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}]
32:["$","h2","43",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"What NOT to Do"}]
33:["$","ul","44",{"className":"list-disc list-outside ml-5 space-y-1 text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","children":[["$","li","0",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Never use paper towels</strong> — they scratch the playing surface"}}],["$","li","1",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Never use household glass cleaner or alcohol</strong> — they strip the groove walls"}}],["$","li","2",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Never blow on a record</strong> — the moisture in your breath leaves residue"}}],["$","li","3",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Never clean against the grooves</strong> — always clean in the groove direction (circular)"}}],["$","li","4",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong class=\"text-white\">Never put a wet record back in its sleeve</strong> — moisture trapped in paper causes mold"}}]]}]
34:["$","hr","45",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}]
35:["$","h2","46",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Stylus Cleaning"}]
36:["$","p","47",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Your stylus needs regular cleaning too. A dirty stylus degrades sound quality and re-deposits grime back into clean records."}}]
37:["$","ul","48",{"className":"list-disc list-outside ml-5 space-y-1 text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","children":[["$","li","0",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Use a <strong class=\"text-white\">stylus brush</strong> (a small soft brush) to gently sweep forward-to-back across the stylus tip"}}],["$","li","1",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"For deeper cleaning, <strong class=\"text-white\">stylus cleaning fluid</strong> on a piece of dense foam works well — lower the needle onto the foam gently"}}],["$","li","2",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Never clean side-to-side — the cantilever can snap"}}]]}]
38:["$","hr","49",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}]
39:["$","h2","50",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Building a Tracklist After Cleaning Sessions"}]
3a:["$","p","51",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"After cleaning and playing through a batch of records, use <strong class=\"text-white\">45 Mix Trackr</strong> to record your session and automatically generate a tracklist. It's especially useful when you're sorting through a new thrift store haul and want to catalog what you found."}}]
3b:["$","hr","52",{"className":"border-[#282828] my-8"}]
3c:["$","h2","53",{"className":"text-white text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4","children":"Conclusion"}]
3d:["$","p","54",{"className":"text-[#B3B3B3] leading-relaxed my-3","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Record cleaning is the most underrated maintenance habit in vinyl culture. A ten-second brush before every play, occasional wet cleaning for new additions, and proper stylus care will keep your collection sounding great and your equipment lasting longer. Think of it as regular maintenance — like changing the oil in a car."}}]
